{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/listen-to-pdf-file-using-python-text-to-speech-library-a33142811927", "time": 1683017043.038363, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/listen-to-pdf-file-using-python-text-to-speech-library-a33142811927/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Listen to PDF file using Python Text to Speech Library | by Renu Khandelwal | Towards Data Science", "h1": "Listen to PDF file using Python Text to Speech Library", "description": "This short article explores the text to speech Python library pyttxs3, reads the PDF files and converts the text to audio, and adjusts the listening speed and volume. My daughter wanted a program\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [], "all_paragraphs": ["This short article explores the text to speech Python library pyttxs3, reads the PDF files and converts the text to audio, and adjusts the listening speed and volume.", "My daughter wanted a program that she can use to listen to a PDF file, an HTML file, or a word document. She wanted to adjust the speed and the volume of the audio and this was my quick solution for her problem using a python text to speech library.", "Import the python text to the speech library: pyttsx3, initialize the library, then pass the text to say(), and finally, flush the say() queue to play the text as audio.", "We will read the PDF file using PyPDF2.", "Set the rate and volume properties to manage the audio speed and volume.", "If you are an audio person, then you now know the basics for text to speech; you can try to listen to HTML pages, doc files, etc., and explore the possibilities.", "pyttsx3 is a simple to use text to speech conversion library and allows you to read any text from a PDF file, a text, a doc file, or an HTML page and listen to it like an audio book.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "A Technology Enthusiast who constantly seeks out new challenges by exploring cutting-edge technologies to make the world a better place